---------------------------------------------------
Welcome to the package which takes HZZ4l inputs, creates datacards 
for the limit calculation, and provides scripts for running the limits 
both locally and on the grid

by Matt Snowball 
---------------------------------------------------

Getting started...
cvs co -P -r <tag> -d Limits UserCode/HZZ4L_Combination/CombinationPy

Functions:
0. Take inputs from HZZ4l analysis and convert to datacard inputs
Documentation: AnalysisInputs/README

1. Create datacards for running with LandS or Combination
Documentation: CreateDatacards/README

2. Run SignalSeparation
Documentation: SignalSeparation/MEKD/README

#########################################################

1. Create datacards for running with LandS or Combination

### Q U I C K   S T A R T   R E C I P E
## Getting setup...
cmsrel CMSSW_6_1_1
cd CMSSW_6_1_1/src/
cvs co -r V03-01-00 HiggsAnalysis/CombinedLimit
cmsenv
scram b -j12
cd ../..
## compile HCSaW
./buildPackage.sh
## check inputs ---> SM_inputs_7TeV and SM_inputs_8TeV
## 2D signal separation
python makeDCsandWSs.py -b -i <input directory> -a <output name> -t <templateDir>

## or 1D signal separation
python makeDCsandWSs.py -b -i <input directory> -a <output name> -t <templateDir> --unfold

## this will unfold the 2D templates and use TH1Fs and plain root files 
## all yields etc should be identical between the 2 cases

## or you can use buildAllCards.py to make all of your cards and workspaces
## for each model and put them in the HCG_<1D or 2D>_<model> directories

#look into buildAllCards.py and set the models list to what you want to build
# then run it with

	$ python buildAllCards.py

